      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is motivated by trying to integrate SkYUVAPixmapInfo into chrome. Chrome\u0027s image generator code thinks in terms of bit depth, with one value for Y, U, and V. Having to construct color types was making the integration painful.\n\nChrome\u0027s SkImageGenerator subclass currently only succeeds the YUV query if the planes are 8 bit (because our old API is explicitly tri-planar 8bit). The SupportedDataTypes thing here is looking ahead to relaxing that in Chrome but only when the GrContext supports it.",
      "revId": "d9487e98e1b756fdb52ca95ed8aba635c9649537",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
